The finance ministry, together with business leaders, has been working to avert a possible credit rating downgrade to junk status. CAPE TOWN Cabinet has called for a united front as international credit rating agencies prepare to assess South Africa s credit-worthiness.The finance ministry, together with business leaders, has been pulling out all the stops in a bid to avert a possible downgrade to junk status.Minister in the Presidency Jeff Radebe says international ratings agencies Moody s, Fitch and Standard &amp; Poor's will, in the coming weeks announce their decision. Our government has been working with business society and labour to translate our country s plans into concrete actions that will ensure South Africa remains an investment grade country. Government calls all sectors to join government in a united front to protect the country s investment status. (Edited by Masechaba Sefularo)